name: Unidentified_man_(Five_Points_Station)
content:
A human man resided at Five Points station in the Outer Rim Territories. The man, born around 31 BBY, was about ten years older than the fugitive slicer Jyn Erso.
When Erso was eighteen years old and staying on Five Points in 3 BBY, the man solicited her sexually. Erso noticed the man's rough knuckles, which led her to believe he often used his fists in combat. She rejected the man's advances, and in response, he called her a "coldhearted Kath." Erso pickpocketed the man while he was making overtures to her, later giving the stolen credits to a Huloon beggar at the station.
The man appeared in Beth Revis' 2017 novel Rebel Rising.
